8,0.14760467,-0.01732795,-0.00920274,-0.01222025,0.00682471,0.04821244,0.05264932,-0.01978949,0.00391465,0.00753563,0.10796290,0.04594083,0.05900826,0.02564295,-0.02247549,0.08209930,0.03679332,-0.01750757,0.00921083,0.02197265,-0.00781320,-0.01071136,0.08209565,-0.06129713,-0.01013303,-0.06395311,0.02608998,-0.02708838,-0.01998772,-0.08057345,-0.05299126,0.03109853,-0.00275617,0.05164858,0.04308705,-0.02110951,-0.04614375,0.07679083,0.00545211,0.02109977,0.06243957,0.03041710,0.02242080]',E'Jenkins cron syntax\n\nBeware that for the day of month field, short cycles such as `\\*/3` or `H/3` will not work consistently near the end of most months, due to variable month lengths.\nFor example, `*/3` will run on the 1st, 4th, …31st days of a long month, then again the next day of the next month.\nHashes are always chosen in the 1-28 range, so `H/3` will produce a gap between runs of between 3 and 6 days at the end of a month.','{"source": "jenkins", "version": "2.4", "language": "groovy", "title": "Syntax.Adoc", "section_title": "syntax.adoc", "url": "https://github.com/jenkins-infra/jenkins.io/blob/master/content/doc/book/pipeline/syntax.adoc", "topics": "jenkins,ci,pipeline,syntax.adoc", "categories": "devops,ci,automation"}');
