129235,-0.00614117,-0.02336636,-0.00298471,-0.02858609,0.02869463,-0.03329811,-0.04370363,0.01700896,-0.04988260,0.04534068,-0.03512404,0.04186609,0.06350160,0.02676713,0.00994385,0.02850797,0.04971482,0.00044526,0.03212454,-0.11618059,0.01259084,0.02801989,-0.10463616,-0.04087535,-0.01090914,-0.02450060,0.00989598,-0.08530141,-0.04409450,-0.00946212,-0.00986863,0.12086871,0.03123855,0.01658395,0.02038092,-0.00452739,0.01165672,0.00780951,-0.10451516,0.12584287,-0.01033777,0.06792961]',E'List installed plugins and their versions\n\nThe simplest way to retrieve the list of installed plugins and their versions is by using the Jenkins Script Console.\n\nFollow these steps:\n\n1. Open the Jenkins link:/doc/book/managing/script-console/[Script Console]:\n\n   - Navigate to `Manage Jenkins` > `Script Console`.\n2. Run the following script to list installed plugins and their versions:\n\n\n[source,groovy]\n----\n   Jenkins.instance.pluginManager.plugins.each {\n      println("${it.getShortName()}: ${it.getVersion()}")\n   }\n----\n\nThis script iterates through each installed plugin and prints its short name along with the version.','{"source": "jenkins", "version": "2.4", "language": "groovy", "title": "Plugins.Adoc", "section_title": "plugins.adoc", "url": "https://github.com/jenkins-infra/jenkins.io/blob/master/content/doc/book/managing/plugins.adoc", "topics": "jenkins,ci,pipeline,plugins.adoc", "categories": "devops,ci,automation"}');
